SOME EXEMPLES OF THE LU (Language for the User) USING :
=======================================================
(low or up case letters are not significant)

 3 ; 7e5 ;  -(3+4)/7;   { 3 arithmetical expressions }

defvar Pi; Pi=atan(1)*4; {the Pi constant }

defvar R,circumference;
R=1e3 ; circumference= 2 * pi * R ; 
                                      
deffunc g( no , x );
if no=1 then g=no ;
        else g=x ;
endif; 
endfunc; 
g(1,2);
g(2,3);

deffunc k(n);        { one bad example with goto! }
deflab lab1,lab2;
goto lab2;
lab1: k=n*n;
return;
lab2: goto lab1;
endfunc;   

deffunc f(n);        { Example of for }
   defvar i; 
   f=1;
   for i=1 to n ;
      f=f*i;
   endfor;
endfunc;
f(5); 

deffunc fa(n);       { Example of while }
   defvar i;
   fa=1; i=0; 
   while i<n ;
      i=i+1 ;
      fa=fa*i ;
   endwhile;
endfunc; 
fa(5);  

deffunc fac(n);       { Example of repeat ... until }
   defvar i;
   fac=1; 
   i=0;
   repeat
      i=i+1; 
      fac=fac*i;
   until i=n;
endfunc;
fac(5); 

deffunc puiss2( n );     { Example to display values }
defvar i;
for i=1 to n;
   display 2**i;
endfor;
endfunc;
puiss2(16); 
   
deffunc h(n); h=n+n; endfunc; h(5);
{ a function may be call an other function }      
deffunc k(n); k=h(h(n)) ; endfunc; k(5);

deffunc maxi(x,y,z);       { Function max with 3 parameters }
maxi=max(x,max(y,z));
endfunc;

deffunc maxim(x,y,z,t,u);  { Function max with 5 parameters }
maxim=maxi(x,y,maxi(z,t,u));
endfunc;
maxim(1,2,3,4,5);

deffunc maximum(x,y,z,t,u,v); { Variante with 6 parameters }
maximum=max(maxi(x,y,maxi(z,t,u)),v);
display maximum;
endfunc;
maximum(1,2,3,6,5,4); 

display ~>ligne>axe>xyzsommet(nbsom);

DefVar varut; varut=12;
display ~>surface>s>xyzsommet(xyzsom(varut)(3))

{End of examples of language LU using }


SPECIAL FUNCTIONS USED BY MEFISTO
=================================
(low or up-case letters are not significant)
The name of the function is significant
The name of every parameter is not significant but its number
in the list is significant.
These parameters can be used or not, but have to be present
in the definition of the function.
All these parameters will be initialized during the call of the function.


DefFunc TAILLE_IDEALE( x, y, z );  or equivalently
DefFunc EDGE_LENGTH( x, y, z );
EDGE_LENGTH = the wished length of edges around the point (x,y,z) of
Finite Elements during the construction of meshes for particular options
as automatic triangulations or tetrahedrizations.
Valuable during the execution of MAILLER


DefFunc REGION( time, x, y, z );
REGION=1 if you want the values of the solution is displayed
for these values of time and the point (x,y,z)
REGION=0 the solution is not displayed

The solution may be the temperature (THERMICER),
the displacement, the stress (ELASTICER).


For THERMICER -----------------------------------------------------

DefFunc CONDUCTIVITY( TIME, X, Y, Z, NO_TYPE_SVO, NO_SVO, TEMPER ); 
CONDUCTIVITY = The ISOTROPIC HEAT CONDUCTIVITY at time ant point X,Y,Z, 
for the SURFACE if 2d OBJECT => NO_TYPE_SVO=3,
or VOLUME if 3d OBJECT => NO_TYPE_SVO=4,
or OBJECT => NO_TYPE_SVO=5,
of type number NO_TYPE_SVO (3:SURFACE, 4:VOLUME, 5:OBJECT)
the lexicon number NO_SVO
for a temperature TEMPER
 
EXAMPLE:
deffunc conductivity( t, x, y, z, no_type_objet, material, temper ) ;
if   material=nuobjt( 'volume' , 'steel' )
then conductivity= 20;
else if   material=nuobjt( 'volume' , 'copper' )
     then conductivity=52;
     else conductivity=0 ;
     endif;  
endif;
endfunc; 

Remark:
- If the material is ANISOTROPIC, the values of the symmetric tensor
of conductivity must be given. A 8-th parameter appears in 
DefFunc CONDUCTIVITY( TIME, X, Y, Z, NO_TYPE_SVO, NO_SVO, TEMPER, nuc );
where nuc is the number of the tensor coefficient to initialize.

- The LU function nuobjt( p1, p2 ) gives the
number of the PLSVO of type p1 with the name p2.


DefFunc SOURCE( T, X, Y, Z, NO_TYPE_OBJET, NO_OBJET, TEMPER );
SOURCE = HEAT SOURCE at time and point X,Y,Z
at time T, at point X,Y,Z, 
for the PLSVO of type number NO_TYPE_OBJECT
(1:POINT, 2:LINE, 3:SURFACE, 4:VOLUME, 5:OBJECT )
the lexicon number NO_OBJECT
for a temperature TEMPER, known or unknown (not linear case)
 
EXAMPLE:
deffunc source( t, x, y, z, no_type_objet, material, temper );
if  material=nuobjt( 'ligne' , 'neumann' )
then 
  source=1e3; 
else
  if  material=nuobjt( 'ligne' , 'fourier' )
  then 
    source=20;
  else
    source=0
  endif;   
endif;
endfunc; 


DefFunc HTCOEFFICIENT( T, X, Y, Z, NO_TYPE_OBJET, NO_OBJET, TEMPER  ) ;
HTCOEFFICIENT = the HEAT TRANSFER COEFFICIENT
on a part of the object boundary (Fourier-Robin boundary condition)
at time T, at point X,Y,Z, 
for the PLS of type number NO_TYPE_OBJECT
(1:POINT, 2:LINE, 3:SURFACE )
the lexicon number NO_OBJECT
for a temperature TEMPER, known or unknown (not linear case)

EXAMPLE:
deffunc HTCoef( t, x, y, z, no_type_objet, material, temper ) ;
if   material=nuobjt( 'surface' , 'air' )
then HTCoef= 750;
else if   material=nuobjt( 'surface' , 'water' )
     then HTCoef=900;
     else HTCoef=0 ;
     endif;  
endif;
endfunc; 



DEfFunc FIXTEMPERATURE( T, X, Y, Z, NO_TYPE_OBJECT, NO_OBJECT, TEMPER );
FIXTEMPERATURE = Value of the imposed temperature (Dirichlet condition)
at time TEMPS, at point X,Y,Z, 
for the PLSVO of type number NO_TYPE_OBJECT
(1:POINT, 2:LINE, 3:SURFACE, 4:VOLUME, 5:OBJECT )
the lexicon number NO_OBJECT
for a temperature TEMPER, known or unknown

EXAMPLE:
deffunc TEMPERATURE( t, x, y, z, no_type_objet, materiau, temper );
if   materiau=nuobjt( 'surface' , 'dirichlet0' )
then TEMPERATURE=0; 
else
  if   materiau=nuobjt( 'surface' , 'contact100' )
  then TEMPERATURE= 100;
  endif;   
endif;
endfunc; 


DefFunc TEMPERATURE_EXACTE(t,x,y,z); or equivalently
DefFunc EXACT_TEMPERATURE(t,x,y,z);

TEMPERATURE_EXACTE = Value of the temperature, supposed known,
at time t, at point x,y,z.
This function permits to display the exact solution, the computed solution,
the error at nodes, ... from a known solution described by an arithmetical
expression.
This function is useful to appreciate the accuracy of the method to find
this solution.


